-- Nordic Stocks: Det Norske, Loomis, Sevan, Eitzen Maritime Services Move
-- B y   A d a m   E w i n g   a n d   C h r i s t i a n   W i e n b e r g
-- 2010-11-05T13:57:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/nordic-stocks-decline-det-norske-loomis-sevan-stora-shares-are-active.html
The  Stoxx Nordic 30 Index , the
benchmark measure for the region, fell 0.7 percent to 7,031.06
at 2:57 p.m. in Stockholm, paring yesterday’s gain.  Norway’s  OBX Index  lost 0.2 percent. The  OMX Helsinki 25
Index  retreated 0.2 percent, while Denmark’s  Copenhagen 20 Index 
was unchanged. The Swedish market closed 1 p.m. local time today
for a public holiday with a 1 percent loss for the  OMX Stockholm
30 Index .  The following companies’ shares were among the most active
in Nordic markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  Det Norske Oljeselskap ASA  (DETNOR NO) tumbled 4.2 percent
to 25.10 kroner, the biggest drop since Aug. 11. The oil and gas
explorer reported a third-quarter net loss of 80.1 million
kroner ($13.9 million).  Eitzen Maritime Services ASA  (EMS NO) surged the most since
March, soaring 38 percent to 1.13 kroner. The Norwegian supplier
of services for the shipping industry won a $100 million order
from the navy of an unnamed European member of NATO.  HKScan Oyj  (HKSAV FH) rose for a third day in four, gaining
1.5 percent to 7.37 euros. The Finnish meat company reported an
increase in third-quarter net income and reaffirmed its full-
year earnings predictions.  Loomis AB  (LOOMB SS) climbed 4.2 percent to 86.75 kroner,
the highest price in six months. The armored car unit spun off
from Securitas AB said profit after tax in the third quarter was
157 million kronor compared with 142 million kronor ($21.5
million) a year earlier. The average estimate of seven analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg was for profit of 146.1 million kronor.  Norwegian Air Shuttle AS  (NAS NO) rose for a third day,
gaining 6.1 percent to 95.25 kroner. The Norwegian discount
carrier said October passenger traffic climbed 21 percent
compared with the same month last year.  Sevan Marine ASA  (SEVAN NO) fell 8.2 percent to 6.92
kroner, the biggest decline since Aug. 18. The maker of offshore
oil and gas equipment’s Sevan Driller rig had a malfunction with
its blow-out preventer. which started on Nov. 2. The company
will work the supplier of the blow-out preventer, Cameron
International Corp., to fix the problem.  Stora Enso Oyj  (STERV FH) fell 1.6 percent to 7.30 euros,
paring four days of gains. Europe’s largest papermaker will
exercise its right to redeem its $421 million bond maturing in
May 2011. The redemption will take place on Dec. 9, the company
said.  Vaisala Oyj  (VAIAS FH) lost the most since June 23, sinking
3.6 percent to 21.20 euros. The world’s biggest maker of
electronic humidity measurement devices lowered its full-year
forecast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
